judgement.reason: An unfolded protein response factor is a regulatory element involved in the unfolded protein response, while an unfolded protein response protein is a broader term that includes any protein involved in the unfolded protein response, including but not limited to regulatory factors.

An unfolded protein response (UPR) sensor is a specific type of protein that detects misfolded proteins in the endoplasmic reticulum, whereas an unfolded protein response protein could refer to any protein involved in the UPR pathway, not necessarily a sensor.
The terms 'Unfolded Protein Response (UPR) protein' and 'unfolded protein response protein' refer to the same concept, with the latter being a non-abbreviated form of the former.
ER stress sensors are a subset of proteins involved in the unfolded protein response, but not all unfolded protein response proteins are ER stress sensors.

The unfolded protein response is a cellular stress response related to the endoplasmic reticulum stress, whereas an unfolded protein response protein refers to specific proteins involved in this response. Not all aspects of the unfolded protein response are limited to these proteins.

An unfolded protein response (UPR) sensor is a specific type of protein involved in detecting misfolded proteins, whereas an unfolded protein response protein can refer to any protein involved in the UPR pathway, not just the sensors.
